  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). All project requirements documented in the credibility assessment plan are addressed in the factor rationales below; the package conforms to the Minimal profile binding convention.",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cou1-hemolysis-cpb",
